00:00:02.928 --> 00:00:03.550
Hey, everyone.

00:00:03.550 --> 00:00:04.050
What's up?

00:00:04.050 --> 00:00:04.900
It's Rob Dodson.

00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:07.250
Palmer 1.0 is in the
house and today, I'm

00:00:07.250 --> 00:00:09.850
going to introduce you to the
brand new Polymer Starter Kit.

00:00:09.850 --> 00:00:11.470
So come on down and
let's get hacking.

00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:18.370
So Polymer Starter Kit is
brand new opinionated scaffold

00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:20.050
for building
Polymer apps, and it

00:00:20.050 --> 00:00:23.220
is jam packed full of awesome.

00:00:23.220 --> 00:00:26.050
Out of the box, it provides
a really nice layout

00:00:26.050 --> 00:00:30.480
that leverages the latest
1.0 material design elements.

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:33.620
It also has support for theming
using custom properties,

00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:35.940
and we showed these off
in the last episode.

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:37.740
Now you're seeing it
kind of at a bigger

00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:39.424
scale, which is really cool.

00:00:39.424 --> 00:00:41.590
The other really awesome
thing about the Starter Kit

00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:43.820
is that it comes
with optional support

00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:46.620
for offline first
development, which

00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:49.840
means in your
application, you can go.

00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:54.030
You could set it into Airplane
mode, refresh the browser,

00:00:54.030 --> 00:00:56.571
and everything would still load.

00:00:56.571 --> 00:00:58.320
You could even navigate
to different pages

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.530
within your application.

00:00:59.530 --> 00:01:01.420
Things would still work.

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:03.590
What's doing this
magic behind the scenes

00:01:03.590 --> 00:01:05.725
is a new technology
called Service Worker,

00:01:05.725 --> 00:01:08.100
and I'm going to talk more
about that in a future episode

00:01:08.100 --> 00:01:10.757
because it's just so cool.

00:01:10.757 --> 00:01:11.840
So how do you get started?

00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:13.490
Well, there's two approaches.

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:16.140
You could head over to the
Polymer Starter Kit home page

00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:17.890
and download the zip bundle.

00:01:17.890 --> 00:01:19.980
That is one way to do it.

00:01:19.980 --> 00:01:21.920
Or, if you want to
be a hotshot like me,

00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:24.614
you can install the
Polymer Yeoman Generator.

00:01:24.614 --> 00:01:27.030
The generator pulls down the
latest version of the Starter

00:01:27.030 --> 00:01:30.006
Kit so anytime you want to
just spin up a new project,

00:01:30.006 --> 00:01:31.380
you just go to
your command line,

00:01:31.380 --> 00:01:35.400
you type "yo polymer," and
boom, you're ready to rock.

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:38.040
Now, once you're set up,
bust open your editor

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:40.240
and this is what you should see.

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:41.820
The files in the
root of the project

00:01:41.820 --> 00:01:44.900
are dedicated to things
like package management--

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:51.250
I've got a package JSON here--
linters with JSNRC and JSCSRC.

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:54.840
So all this is build type stuff.

00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:57.940
Up here in the App
Directory, this

00:01:57.940 --> 00:02:00.720
is actually where all of
the UI for my application

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:02.470
is going to live.

00:02:02.470 --> 00:02:04.700
And because I downloaded
the version that

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:07.180
has support for the
Gulp build process,

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:09.600
I've also got a Gulp file here.

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:12.840
But if you went with the light
version which doesn't include

00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:13.980
Gulp, that's totally fine.

00:02:13.980 --> 00:02:16.063
You don't necessarily need
this for this tutorial,

00:02:16.063 --> 00:02:19.080
but I just want you to
know that that's there.

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:21.480
So all of these files might
seem really overwhelming,

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:22.382
but don't panic.

00:02:22.382 --> 00:02:23.840
There's tons of
great stuff in here

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:25.840
and I'm going to help
walk you through all of it

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:27.580
over the next few
episodes of Polycast.

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:29.825
For today, let's just
start really small.

00:02:29.825 --> 00:02:31.450
We're going to preview
the app and then

00:02:31.450 --> 00:02:34.400
we're going to update
some of the theme colors.

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:36.715
Now, because the Starter
Kit uses Gulp for its

00:02:36.715 --> 00:02:39.090
build process, I'm going to
hop onto my terminal and type

00:02:39.090 --> 00:02:41.405
out "gulp serve," which will
put boot a local server,

00:02:41.405 --> 00:02:44.050
and it's even going to
open my browser for me,

00:02:44.050 --> 00:02:45.130
which is pretty awesome.

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:49.550
Nice.

00:02:49.550 --> 00:02:51.390
Now, if you're using
the light version

00:02:51.390 --> 00:02:53.090
of the site which
doesn't include Gulp,

00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:55.250
you can use your own server.

00:02:55.250 --> 00:02:57.810
So here, I'm just booting
up Python simple HTTP server

00:02:57.810 --> 00:02:59.449
on port 3,000.

00:02:59.449 --> 00:03:01.740
And then I would need to go
and open my browser myself,

00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:03.520
but this is an option
for the folks who

00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:04.760
downloaded that version.

